skip     1
fields   date,inputTokens,outputTokens,cacheCreationTokens,cacheReadTokens,totalTokens,totalCost
account1 (ai)

# 1 token corresponds very roughly to 3 characters. There are four types:
#
# input tokens:        user prompts, anything new that wasn't cached
# cache create tokens: system prompt, file content, tool output, message history
# cache read tokens:   history being reread from cache on every turn
# output tokens:       generated by the AI
#
# Output tokens are the most significant for energy use; cache create are next.
# Simplest rough measure of AI's work: output
# Best rough measure of energy use: output + 0.5 * cache create.
# Thinking effort reflected in the token counts.
# Model is not; smarter models' tokens cost much more than dumber models.
# My tokens are mostly opus (4.6+); assume all are.
#
# Equivalences (ballpark):
# 1 opus output token =~
#  10 joules
#  0.0028 Wh
#  0.05 mL water
#  Lifting a 1 kg bag of sugar 1 meter
#  A 10W LED running for 1 second (or a 100W bulb for 1/10 s)
#  A laptop running for ~0.2 seconds at typical 50W load
#  ~1/700th of an AA battery (a fully charged AA stores ~7 kJ)
#  ~1/5,000th of an iPhone battery charge (~50 kJ)
#  ~1/200th of a kitchen match (a match releases ~2 kJ when burned)
#  Heating one drop of water by ~50 °C (a drop is ~50 mg; 10 J takes it from room temp to nearly boiling)
#  ~10 human heartbeats' worth of mechanical work (heart does ~1 J/beat)
#  ~0.0024 food calories (a single raisin is ~4 kcal = ~17 kJ, so one token ≈ 1/1,700 of a raisin)
#  Roughly 1/30th of a traditional Google search (older estimates put a search at ~300 J, though modern numbers are lower)
#
# Tokens are easily wasted: check/minimise context (MCPs, memory, long chat histories), and reduce effort.
# Switch to a dumber model for cheaper tokens.
# The dominant environmental lever is the grid mix powering the datacenter, not the raw token count — same model on hydro-powered infrastructure vs. coal differs by ~10× on carbon.

#amount1  %totalTokens t @@ $%totalCost

amount1  %outputTokens opus_output_tokens @@ $%totalCost


